Genes for Good is a Facebook app designed to survey the health of millions of users . 
  It was set up by the University of Michigan and is available for free to people aged over 18 in the US . 
  Users can submit spit samples to tie their survey results to their genes . 
  The app is hosted by Facebook but the site is not affiliated with the scheme . 
  It is voluntary and is only available to people with a valid US mailing address . 
 